Critical analysiation on the quote "And if happiness visits you again, do not remember
it's previous betrayal. Enter into happiness and burst"

This quote teaches us not to remember when happiness that has failed 
us, like a person who has been unfaithful in the past (do not remember
it's previous betrayal). This makes it seem like past memories are just
obsacles in the way of true happiness, oversimplifying the human psychology
that proves that painful memories can shpae the way we act and do things 
in our daily lives.

Happiness in this quote is described as something that can 'visit' or 'betray'
us, this is a technique calle personification meaning describing an object as
a livng human being. This proves the point that many people don;t want happiness
because it's unrilable. This implies that happiness isn't always a consistent 
feeling and relying on it can lead to betrayal.

The phrase "Enter into happiness and burst" suggests that when a person let's
go of fear and hesitation, happiness can totally immersing with us. It promotes
letting go of fear and hesitation for something that brings joy to our soul.
But some realise that letting go isn't that easy for some people, and sometimes it
can destroy a person more than fixing them.

Overall this quote teaches us that life is unpredictable depending on what you 
believe and don't believe. And that letting go isn't easy for everyone and when 
they do let go, they'll find a life worth living for.
